                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.002/651: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-05-14T14:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 14, 1938—2 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>170. Your 300, May 7, 1 p.m., and Shanghai’s 649, May 12, 6 p.m., Chinese
                    Maritime Customs. After careful consideration of the information and comment
                    contained in the telegrams under reference, the Department desires that you make
                    an approach to the Japanese Foreign Office along the lines of the Department’s
                    telegram 157, May 4, 6 p.m.</p>
                <p>You may inform your British and French colleagues of your action.</p>
                <p>Repeat to Shanghai for Hankow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
